export [VAR=value | VAR | (none)]

Set, query, or list environment variables.

  export VAR=value   Set VAR to value
  export VAR         Print the current value of VAR
  export             List all variables (sorted)

Variables are expanded with $VAR or ${VAR} in any command line.

Built-in variables: HOME, SHELL, PWD (updated by cd).

Examples:
  export GREETING=hello
  echo $GREETING
  echo ${GREETING} world
  export PWD
  export
